4
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:59,500
Ms. Liang, here is Jiang Qiao Xi's medical fee.

5
00:02:10,140 --> 00:02:12,740
Anything else to say?

6
00:02:12,740 --> 00:02:18,400
Ms. Liang, Jiang Qiao Xi is my classmate.

7
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:20,810
And I want to be friends with him.

8
00:02:22,779 --> 00:02:24,879
Be friends?

9
00:02:27,099 --> 00:02:30,719
Don't you have more important things to do?

10
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:35,360
Is making friends the main purpose of your life?

11
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:39,800
I'm only trying to live my life to the full.

12
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:43,700
I care about my friends, family, and school life.

13
00:02:43,700 --> 00:02:47,019
But Jiang Qiao Xi should focus
on the Olympiad.

14
00:02:47,019 --> 00:02:52,060
He's so talented. He's going to the International Olympiad.

15
00:02:52,659 --> 00:02:56,460
How does our friendship hold him back?

16
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:03,600
You're driving a wedge between us.

17
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:15,340
Back then, you tricked me into your backyard
and told me to love Jiang Qiao Xi more.

18
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:17,659
Can you promise me

19
00:03:18,459 --> 00:03:22,900
that you'll love Jiang Qiao Xi more
if he returns to the provincial city with you?

20
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:27,020
He doesn't like black that much.
His favorite color is red.

21
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:31,439
His favorite animal is rabbits.
His favorite food is date buns.

22
00:03:31,439 --> 00:03:34,699
Remember to add milk if you make them for him.

23
00:03:34,699 --> 00:03:37,479
It's tastier like that.

24
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:42,819
I found it ridiculous
that a child was telling me those things.

25
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:49,860
I had a major hemorrhage during his birth
and had 36 bags of blood transfusions.

26
00:03:49,860 --> 00:03:53,290
I shed every drop of my blood for him.

27
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:58,460
No one could love him more than I do.

28
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:05,240
Like his brother, Jiang Qiao Xi showed
exceptional math talent from a young age.

29
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,620
So my mission is

30
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:12,319
to escort him
to the International Olympiad and remove all obstacles for him.

31
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:16,339
I must ensure he reaches the destination.

32
00:04:17,620 --> 00:04:24,379
But you're making him deviate from his path.

33
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:30,779
I've never hindered his academic performance.

34
00:04:30,779 --> 00:04:36,499
He's defied me again and again because of you.

35
00:04:37,099 --> 00:04:42,940
Cherry, if you truly care about him
and want what's best for him,

36
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,720
please stay away from him.

37
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:54,020
Otherwise, he might never get
what he deserves because of you.

38
00:04:56,679 --> 00:05:03,139
More importantly, you'll ruin our relationship.

39
00:05:03,139 --> 00:05:07,440
Then I'll lose my son.

40
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:13,079
And Jiang Qiao Xi will lose his mother.

41
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:22,779
I-I wouldn't...

42
00:05:24,719 --> 00:05:25,859
I wouldn't...

43
00:05:25,859 --> 00:05:33,460
That's right, you wouldn't, Cherry.
You're a good girl.

44
00:05:33,460 --> 00:05:37,520
You've made the right choice as a kid.

45
00:05:38,259 --> 00:05:43,920
So I'm sure you know
what to do as a grown-up. Am I right?

46
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:18,299
 More importantly, you will ruin our relationship. 

47
00:06:19,060 --> 00:06:23,339
 Then I'll lose my son. 

48
00:06:23,339 --> 00:06:27,579
 And Jiang Qiao Xi will lose his mother. 

49
00:06:37,059 --> 00:06:39,159
- Hello? 
 - Hello? Cherry?

50
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:45,420
Jiang Qiao Xi? Are you allowed to call me?

51
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:47,620
They're not home.

52
00:06:48,299 --> 00:06:51,520
How are you? Are you hurting?

53
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:58,200
Cherry, I'm resting at home
and don't have to attend the training camp.

54
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:02,299
Can you bring me some date buns
and lotus root sandwiches after school tomorrow?

55
00:07:02,299 --> 00:07:06,700
I-I...

56
00:07:08,859 --> 00:07:11,779
I'll see what I can do tomorrow.

57
00:07:11,779 --> 00:07:14,799
Rest early. Sleep well and get better.

58
00:07:14,799 --> 00:07:17,720
I'm going to bed too. Bye.

59
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:40,359
- Yu Qiao, go for it!
- Yu Qiao.

60
00:07:40,359 --> 00:07:42,620
Yu Qiao, go for it!

61
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:44,960
Yu Qiao, you can do it!

62
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,560
- Yu Qiao.
- Yu Qiao.

63
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,460
Come on!

64
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:49,300
- Come on, Yu Qiao!
- Yu Qiao.

65
00:07:49,300 --> 00:07:51,099
Let's go.

66
00:07:51,099 --> 00:07:52,220
Come on, Yu Qiao!

67
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:54,839
Yu Qiao!

68
00:07:57,659 --> 00:08:00,740
Cherry, what's wrong? Yu Qiao won.

69
00:08:00,740 --> 00:08:04,100
Nothing. I'm happy for him.

70
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:07,859
Lin Cherry, something's off with you.

71
00:08:07,859 --> 00:08:09,559
Nonsense.

72
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,340
Hello, Ms. Cao.

73
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,320
What's wrong?

74
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,359
Qin Ye Yun.

75
00:08:28,359 --> 00:08:29,679
Yu Qiao, congratulations.

76
00:08:29,679 --> 00:08:31,899
Something came up. I have to go home.

77
00:08:31,899 --> 00:08:33,700
I'll go with her.

78
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:36,260
Why does Qin Ye Yun look so pale?

79
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:38,040
Did something happen to Mr. Qin again?

80
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:41,059
Probably. Ms. Cao just called.

81
00:08:41,059 --> 00:08:42,600
Let's hurry over then.

82
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:45,020
Yu Qiao, don't worry. My mom's there.

83
00:08:45,020 --> 00:08:49,220
Besides, Qin Ye Yun
wouldn't want us to get involved.

84
00:08:49,220 --> 00:08:53,279
True, although we're kind of free
to leave during the sports meet,

85
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:57,240
we'd better stay and cover for them.

86
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:02,279
Mr. Qin, didn't we agree
that you'd rest in bed at home?

87
00:09:02,279 --> 00:09:05,960
Your leg will worsen if you keep moving around.

88
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:08,579
It's going to be fine.

89
00:09:08,579 --> 00:09:15,199
Don't listen to those doctors.
I know what I'm doing.

90
00:09:15,199 --> 00:09:18,840
My leg will never fully recover.

91
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:22,120
It's a waste of money to get more treatment.

92
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:25,140
My daughter is growing up fast.

93
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:30,720
I can't afford to lose work days
and keep wasting money.

94
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:33,299
Sit down.

95
00:09:33,299 --> 00:09:36,699
Why are you back? You should be at school.

96
00:09:36,699 --> 00:09:38,740
Go back to school now.

97
00:09:38,740 --> 00:09:41,120
I couldn't stop you, so I told Yun.

98
00:09:41,120 --> 00:09:44,319
She rushed back when she heard
you had left the hospital.

99
00:09:44,319 --> 00:09:47,879
I'm fine now. Go back to school.

100
00:09:47,879 --> 00:09:51,579
Come back to the hospital with me
or I'll call an ambulance.

101
00:09:51,579 --> 00:09:56,740
Stop talking nonsense. Call an ambulance?

102
00:09:56,740 --> 00:09:59,740
It'd be a waste of medical resources.

103
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:02,840
I'm better now. It stopped hurting, see?

104
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,340
Dad.

105
00:10:05,299 --> 00:10:10,800
Minor slip-up. No worries.

106
00:10:13,260 --> 00:10:15,319
Dad, I'm quitting school.

107
00:10:15,319 --> 00:10:19,880
What did you say? I dare you to say that again.

108
00:10:19,880 --> 00:10:23,800
I'll find a job tomorrow. I can support myself.

109
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:27,819
Yun, what are you doing?

110
00:10:27,819 --> 00:10:29,799
What are you doing, Yun?

111
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:31,140
Stop.

112
00:10:31,140 --> 00:10:32,959
You can't do this.

113
00:10:32,959 --> 00:10:35,000
I'm tired of it.

114
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,019
I'm tired of you exhausting
yourself for me. I don't need it.

115
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:42,600
What are you doing?

116
00:10:43,199 --> 00:10:46,120
Why are you reading that?

117
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,260
Put it down.

118
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:49,939
What are you doing? Yun. Stop it.

119
00:10:49,939 --> 00:10:52,240
From now on, I'll take care of everything.

120
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:55,500
I promise I'll achieve my dreams on my own.

121
00:10:55,500 --> 00:11:01,139
Qin Ye Yun, you're just a kid.

122
00:11:02,419 --> 00:11:07,480
I'm your father. Shouldn't I
be doing these things for you?

123
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:12,839
But as your daughter, I don't need you
to bear the burdens for me.

124
00:11:13,279 --> 00:11:19,339
With your leg injured like this,
I should be working to sustain us.

125
00:11:19,339 --> 00:11:27,460
Dad, I want you to rest your leg properly
and enjoy some peaceful days.

126
00:11:30,059 --> 00:11:32,612
Although I'm a cripple,

127
00:11:34,308 --> 00:11:41,419
my daughter deserves everything other kids have.

128
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:57,260
Cherry, it's okay. Let's go.

129
00:11:57,260 --> 00:12:03,479
Let them argue it out.
They'll get to understand each other better.

130
00:12:06,740 --> 00:12:08,440
Let's go.

131
00:12:10,260 --> 00:12:20,579
Mom, did you and Dad ever imagine
what kind of person I'd grow up to be?

132
00:12:21,559 --> 00:12:25,439
You'll be happy, like your name suggests.

133
00:12:25,439 --> 00:12:30,819
Your dad's biggest wish is for you to stay happy.

134
00:12:30,819 --> 00:12:32,020
Is that all?

135
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,820
Yeah.

136
00:12:34,699 --> 00:12:38,299
What if I fail this mission?

137
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:41,480
No one can be happy all their life.

138
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:45,460
Are you not our daughter if you're unhappy?

139
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:56,459
But it seems that getting into this high school
is the most impressive thing I've done.

140
00:12:56,459 --> 00:12:59,459
Beyond that, there's nothing special about me.

141
00:12:59,459 --> 00:13:02,480
Aren't you and Dad disappointed?

142
00:13:03,779 --> 00:13:08,440
Guess what's the greatest thing I've ever done.

143
00:13:15,299 --> 00:13:19,940
I gave birth to you. You made me your mom.

144
00:13:24,939 --> 00:13:28,519
Thank you for becoming my mom.

145
00:13:29,559 --> 00:13:33,319
Alright, that's enough, I'm cooking.

146
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:35,179
Now I get it.

147
00:13:35,179 --> 00:13:37,120
What do you get?

148
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:39,940
I just realized something.

149
00:13:41,020 --> 00:13:46,659
I realized that no matter who I become,
you and Dad will always love me.

150
00:14:43,579 --> 00:14:51,279
Ms. Liang, I brought these lotus root sandwiches
and date buns for you and Jiang Qiao Xi.

151
00:15:00,799 --> 00:15:03,200
Do you know what you're doing?

152
00:15:08,339 --> 00:15:14,840
If there's even a slight possibility

153
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:18,159
that Jiang Qiao Xi could lose your love,

154
00:15:19,819 --> 00:15:23,399
then I must stay by his side even more firmly.

